June 9, 2026

****Market Performance****

****Trending on TIKR****

Intel (NASDAQ: INTC): https://app.tikr.com/stock/about?cid=3D21127&tid=3D26=
21295 Intel climbed roughly 10% Monday after announcing a partnership with =
Foxconn at Computex 2026 to build rackscale AI data center infrastructure, =
the latest catalyst repositioning the once-struggling chipmaker as a full-s=
tack AI play. The move also followed reports that Google placed a major ord=
er with Intel's foundry for its TPU AI chips slated for 2028 production, wh=
ile Nvidia is reportedly evaluating Intel's 18A process for future chips. W=
ells Fargo and Barclays both raised price targets toward triple digits. The=
 market is starting to bet that Intel's foundry business, written off by ma=
ny over the past two years, may finally have the hyperscaler validation it =
needs.

Marvell Technology (NASDAQ: MRVL): https://app.tikr.com/stock/about?cid=3D3=
1158&tid=3D2666094 Marvell jumped nearly 10% Monday after S&P Dow Jones Ind=
ices announced the networking and connectivity chip designer will be added =
to the S&P 500 effective June 22. The inclusion creates mechanical buying f=
rom index funds and ETFs, which have to buy the stock to track the benchmar=
k. Marvell designs custom silicon and high-speed connectivity chips that mo=
ve data between AI processors inside data centers, a niche that has become =
critical as training workloads scale. The news lands days after Nvidia CEO =
Jensen Huang publicly called Marvell a future "trillion-dollar company" at =
Computex 2026.

Micron (NASDAQ: MU): https://app.tikr.com/stock/about?cid=3D289030&tid=3D26=
30498 Micron climbed nearly 10% Monday after Nvidia and SK Hynix announced =
a multi-year partnership over the weekend to jointly develop high-bandwidth=
 memory for Nvidia's Vera Rubin AI platform. Micron, already certified as a=
n HBM4 supplier for the same platform and with its entire HBM production fo=
r the rest of fiscal 2026 sold out under long-term contracts, was seen as a=
 direct beneficiary of the AI memory cycle. The move comes ahead of Micron'=
s fiscal Q3 earnings on June 24, where management has guided for a record $=
33.5 billion in revenue. The stock has gone from $37 to nearly $950 in 2026=
.

Brady Corp (NYSE: BRC): https://app.tikr.com/stock/about?cid=3D171296&tid=
=3D2595299 Brady fell about 15% yesterday after the company announced the i=
mmediate retirement of CEO Russell Shaller, with current board member Vinee=
t Nargolwala stepping in as his successor. Brady makes industrial labels, s=
igns, safety devices, and high-speed printing systems used in factories, wa=
rehouses, and data centers. The timing rattled investors because the change=
 comes just months before Brady is set to close its acquisition of Honeywel=
l's Productivity Solutions and Services business, a deal that nearly double=
s its addressable market.

Argan (NYSE: AGX): https://app.tikr.com/stock/about?cid=3D298718&tid=3D7664=
645 Argan slid nearly 11% Monday in what looks like profit-taking after a s=
harp run. The company is an engineering and construction firm that builds l=
arge-scale power plants, particularly natural gas-fired facilities now in h=
eavy demand thanks to AI data center buildouts. Last week Argan reported Q1=
 fiscal 2027 revenue up 50% to a record $291 million, well ahead of the $25=
8 million consensus, and the stock surged over 35% in the days that followe=
d to new all-time highs.

