****The Week Ahead****

5 events that will set the tone for AI cloud, the consumer, housing, and th=
e biggest IPO in history:

**Wednesday, June 10**

*=20

**Chewy (NYSE: CHWY), Before Open:** Online pet supplies retailer Chewy rep=
orts Q1 with consensus EPS of $0.24 on revenue around $3.1 billion. The num=
bers to watch are Autoship subscription growth (which provides recurring re=
venue) and any margin trajectory after the CEO recently called consumers "m=
ore stretched" than at the start of the year. With CHWY down 37% YTD, expec=
tations are low, so an in-line print with steady guidance could move the st=
ock.

*=20

**Oracle (NYSE: ORCL), After Close:** Software giant Oracle reports fiscal =
Q4 with Street looking for EPS of $1.96 on $19.1 billion in revenue. The re=
al focus is on Oracle Cloud Infrastructure growth, where revenue surged 84%=
 last quarter, and the staggering $553 billion remaining performance obliga=
tions backlog that locks in future cloud revenue. Options traders are prici=
ng in a 13% post-earnings move, since this is the cleanest read on AI cloud=
 spending right now.

**Thursday, June 11**

*=20

**Adobe (NASDAQ: ADBE), After Close:** Adobe (Photoshop, Acrobat, and the F=
irefly generative AI suite) reports Q2 with consensus EPS of $5.83 on $6.45=
 billion in revenue. With ADBE down 27% YTD, the stock needs proof that its=
 AI products are converting into actual paid subscription growth, not just =
usage. Firefly recently crossed $250 million in annual recurring revenue. I=
nvestors also want clarity on the CEO succession plan announced in March.

*=20

**Lennar (NYSE: LEN), After Close:** One of the largest US homebuilders rep=
orts Q2 with consensus EPS at $1.24, down roughly 35% year-over-year, on re=
venue of $8.1 billion. The real metrics to watch are new orders (management=
 guided 21,000 to 22,000 homes), deliveries (20,000 to 21,000), and gross m=
argin (15.5% to 16.0%). Any signal that demand is improving or incentive pr=
essure is easing would shift sentiment across the whole homebuilder space.

**Friday, June 12**

*=20

**SpaceX (NASDAQ: SPCX), IPO Day:** SpaceX is set to begin trading Friday a=
t a fixed IPO price of $135, raising roughly $75 billion at a $1.77 trillio=
n valuation. This is the largest IPO ever, more than double Saudi Aramco's =
2019 record. SpaceX builds and launches reusable rockets and operates Starl=
ink, the world's largest satellite internet network. The print will be a ma=
jor test of demand for mega-cap private companies coming public.

